      <trans-unit id="14562" identifier="aa870366a180bbea07105cefddb48077">
        <source>&lt;strong&gt;Extra challenge #1:&lt;/strong&gt;
Write a program that works for any radius.</source>
        <target>crwdns14562:0crwdne14562:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="14563" identifier="1feea79694bd272caa18eda147e44f59">
        <source>That means that it takes a radius as the input then draws a circle with the given radius, and then displays the circumference as the output.</source>
        <target>crwdns14563:0crwdne14563:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="14564" identifier="4127af91e8a713e105e6540398d2d24b">
        <source>&lt;strong&gt;Extra challenge #2:&lt;/strong&gt;
Write a program that takes a circumference as the input then draws a circle with the given circumference and then displays the radius as the output.</source>
        <target>crwdns14564:0crwdne14564:0</target>
        <note>Context: Paragraph text&#13;
XPath: /p[2]</note>
